(19257, 'drug_class', 'N/A', 'severe', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Drug Interactions (not described in Contraindications or Warnings And Precautions) include the following: Drugs Inhibiting or Metabolized by Cytochrome P450: Fluvoxamine inhibits several cytochrome P450 isoenzymes (CYP1A2, CYP2C9, CYP3A4, and CYP2C19). Carbamazepine: Elevated carbamazepine levels and symptoms of toxicity with coadministration (7.2). Sumatriptan: Rare postmarketing reports of weakness, hyperreflexia, and incoordination following use of an SSRI and sumatriptan. Monitor appropriately if concomitant treatment is clinically warranted (7.2). Tacrine: Coadministration increased tacrine Cmax and AUC five- and eight-fold and caused nausea, vomiting, sweating, and diarrhea (7.2). Tricyclic Antidepressants (TCAs): Coadministration significantly increased plasma TC', 'DailyMed'),
